        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 27 at 6:33PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 633 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms with heavy rain extending from 13 miles south of Big
Timber to 11 miles northwest of Red Lodge, moving northeast at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Half inch size hail and heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible. Watch for
localized low land flooding.

Locations impacted include...
Dean, Fishtail, Roscoe, Luther and Mc Leod.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
